{"type":"message","id":"1c675e1c","parentId":"af788728","timestamp":"2026-04-12T02:49:03.910Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I encountered an issue while trying to fetch the latest AI news from the last 24 hours. The `web_search` function requires a Brave Search API key, which I don't have yet. To proceed with this task, you can either configure it using the `openclaw configure --section web` command or set the `BRAVE_API_KEY` environment variable.\n\nOnce configured, try running the search again. Here's how to do that:\n\n1. **Using the CLI**:\n   - Run: `openclaw configure --section web`\n   - Follow the prompts to store your API key.\n   \n2. **Manually setting the environment variable**:\n   - Set: `BRAVE_API_KEY=<your_api_key>`\n\nAfter configuring, you can run the search again using:\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"web_search\",\n  \"arguments\": {\n    \"count\": 5,\n    \"freshness\": \"day\",\n    \"query\": \"latest AI news from last 24 hours focus on LLMs RL Diffusion models VLM robotics\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to assist with this configuration or proceed with a different approach?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8193,"output":244,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8437,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775962143907}}
